        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Imaging requirement:
We propose to image the distribution of the emission of the water (H2O) toward 
the Orion-KL star forming region in band 9 using the C34-4 configuration, 
resulting into an angular resolution of 0.17''.
The maximum detectable source size being 2.8'', we seek to resolve the tiny 
water clump and to filter out the emission arising from the outflow. 
Also, we ask for the high spectral resolution of 0.222 km/s in order to separate
potential line blends

Correlator setup:
Our ALMA-OT science goal will observe 1 baseband of 468.75 MHz. In addition, 
we set one baseband of 937.5 MHz for continuum purpose due to the line 
richness of source. Also, from SMA continuum observations carried out at 
690 GHz by Beuther et al. (2006), we estimated that the continuum peak flux 
density should be about 0.18 Jy per beam. 

Requested sensitivity:
We aim for a sensitivity of 190 mJy per beam which will give us, 
under nominal conditions (pwv of 1.262 mm) and according our model which is 
based on our Herschel observations, a signal-to-noise ratio greater than 10.
This requires a total observing time of 35.50 min.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
